main event: A bright green, circular object was observed moving at a high rate of speed over Bentwaters, England on December 22, 1960.
interesting points: The object was approximately 60-90 feet in size and appeared to have a rotating motion.
The object disappeared behind trees and then reappeared again.
The sighting was made by a military observer who was considered a reliable source.
Another observer in the area thought they saw a 'meteorite' around the same time.
Local radar units, control tower personnel, and pilots were contacted but no corroborating evidence was found.
result: Insufficient information to determine the cause, but the most probable explanation is a 'meteorite-type phenomenon'.
